<br>
a child, realistically, for the most part, does not have the same level of emotional maturity as an adult. a child, realistically, for the most part, does not have the same understanding of anatomy or composition that a trained artist has. if you look at it from the point of view that a picture has to be realistic to be good, then a child's work is poor. however, they are no less valid an an artist.<br>
<br>
all films are art. the seven samurai is art. american pie is art. they are two completely different films, yet they are both art, and therefore both valid forms of expression. <br>
<br>
all paintings are art. van gogh's self portaits are art. picasso's portraits are art. neither are 100% realistic, yet both are art. <br>
<br>
while i do not think of the works of tracey emin or damien hurst to be of very high quality, they are all art, and therefore valid.<br>
<br>
