<br>
of course, the american pie films aren't as good as kurosawa's work. not by a long way. a long, long way. the films kurosawa produced in the soviet union are better than the american pie films. but neither are more legitimate or less ligitimate artforms in their own right. <br>
<br>
something that does differentiate all works of art from each other is historical significance. to return to the american pie/kurosawa example, kurosawa's films are important as cultural and technical landmarks. the cinematography, use of texture and light, and later on, colour - as you rightly say e.p. - all play their part in creating masterpeices of cinema. american pie, on the other hand, is not a masterpeice by any lenght of the imagination. the seven samurai was remade as the magnificent seven, which spawned several sequels, and it's own remake, battle beyond the stars. the original is the best, but the first remake is probably just as important. without starting a new debate, and hopefully without half the planet flaming me, star wars is rubbish. there, i said it. the first one wasn't much cop, the next two were better, the fourth was cronic and i cannot judge the fifth, never having seen it. the plot is stolen from kurosawa, most of the stuff is just oriental rip offs (look at darth vader's helmet, then look at a samuri helmet) and the acting was sporadic. however, it is important historically, amongst other things for being a massive success.<br>
<br>
thank you. and may i remind you this thread is a debate on art, not the merits of star wars...<br>
