<br>
i have very strong opinions about a lot of things, art being one of them. so does alucard, but although both of us have voiced strong opinions in reference to each others posts as well as those of other members, i don't think we've used language that would imply that we are angry. <br>
<br>
alucard: you made an interesting comment about why every one seems to think that art has to have an emotional impact. well, it may just be a question of semantics but i think the argument follows something like this. <br>
a: art is an act of creativity. <br>
b: creativity is a form of expression<br>
c: expression is communication<br>
therefore: lack of communication (in this case usually emotional since we aren't necessarily using words) means lack of expression, means lack of creativity = not art. <br>
<br>
that's kind of condensed, but that's my take on it. of course, some art forms are more complex and do use words (like novels or films) and are capable of communicating more than raw emotion. but really if you look back at a really good film, say Memento, which posits a very interesting commentary on how what we perceive or what we want to perceive shapes our reality, what you remember is usually the gut reaction you had to the whole. yes, the idea may have been communicated well and clearly, but what brought it home was the emotional reaction you had to it. (or at least this is what i usually remember.) <br>
<br>
perhaps i should point out here that i don't believe that all art is equally valid. this is why i consider American Pie entertainment and not art. this is why i think that a crucifix suspended in a jar of urine is not art. <br>
<br>
if you ask me how i make the differentiation, well, i'm not entirely sure myself. it doesn't have anything to do with quality. i simply believe that some art is more valid. <br>
<br>
ooh! i can feel the flames already. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
anyway, just my opinion. you may disagree as you see fit. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
