-If a tree falls in a forest with nobody around, does it make a sound? (In all actuality, no)<br>
-Even if you have a lot of currency, if no one wants it, is it worth anything? (Nope)<br>
-If you make something you intended to be art, and if NO ONE besides yourself actually thinks its art, is it really art? (In my humble opinion, no)<br>
<br>
Therefore, I think the old philosiphy &quot;I think, therefore I am&quot; can be, to an extent, can be used to lead to the conclusion that, frankly, this whole &quot;Validity of art&quot; argument can be answered by; the more people think and accept something as art, the validity of it increases. In retrospect, isn't this pretty obvious? How many people actually think that a child's stick figure is more artistic than Michelangelo's work? No one. The simple fact that the overwhelming majority of people see Mike's work as having more artistic worth in itself increases its validity.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=souridaijin@polykarbonbbs>Souridaijin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/8/03 9:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12617.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.saiyanultimate.com/android186.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: a debate on art and validity...</span><hr size=1> P.S. Can I actually get some feedback this time, guys <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ? I think this point is much better than my last one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=12617.topic&start=21&stop=25>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=12617.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=12617.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br>